        "title": "feat(ui): add collapsible toggle for recent sessions in sidebar",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a collapse/expand toggle to the \"Recent\" sessions section in the web sidebar\n- Follows the exact same pattern as existing nav section groups (Chat, Control, Agent, Settings)\n- The entire \"Recent\" label row is a clickable button with a chevron icon that rotates -90deg when collapsed\n- Collapsed state persists to localStorage via `UiSettings.recentSessionsCollapsed`\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/src/ui/storage.ts` | Add `recentSessionsCollapsed` field and default value |\n| `ui/src/ui/app-render.ts` | Replace static label with collapsible button matching `.nav-section__label` pattern |\n| `ui/src/styles/layout.css` | Add styles matching `.nav-section__label`, `__label-text`, `__chevron` exactly |\n| `ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts` | Add `nav.recentSessionsExpand` / `nav.recentSessionsCollapse` i18n keys |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Sidebar recent sessions section now supports collapse/expand via a toggle button matching the nav section group pattern.\n\nReal environment tested: Local dev server (`pnpm ui:dev`) at http://localhost:5173/, macOS 26, Node 24, pnpm 11.2.2.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. Run `pnpm ui:dev` to start the Control UI dev server\n2. Open http://localhost:5173/ in a browser\n3. Observe the \"Recent\" label in the sidebar — it is now a clickable button with a chevron icon\n4. Click the \"Recent\" button → the session list collapses, chevron rotates clockwise to point right\n5. Click the \"Recent\" button again → the session list expands, chevron rotates back to point down\n6. Refresh the page → collapsed state is preserved from localStorage\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\nExpanded state (chevron down, 5 recent sessions visible, 237px width matching nav groups):\n![Expanded state](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3b7a79d4-4d14-4007-bdfc-fcc879b81be2)\n\nCollapsed state (chevron rotated right, list hidden, only label row visible):\n![Collapsed state](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/045e6469-5121-406d-b38f-6701aea10c6b)\n\nWidth verification via browser DevTools — `.sidebar-recent-sessions__label` computed width 237px, matching `.nav-section__label` exactly:\n```\nrecentLabelWidth: \"237px\"\nnavLabelWidth:    \"237px\"\nmatch:            true\n```\nType checks pass: `pnpm tsgo:core:test` and `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test` both green.\n\nObserved result after fix: Toggle works as expected — click collapses the list (display: none, chevron -90deg), click again expands it (display: grid, chevron 0deg). Width, font-size, padding, color, border-radius, and hover effects all match the adjacent nav section groups exactly. State persists across page refreshes.\n\nWhat was not tested: Mobile viewport responsiveness, non-English i18n locale bundles (only en.ts was updated; other locales require `pnpm ui:i18n:sync` regeneration).\n\nCloses #85510\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
